<div class="c-home-section js-home-section js-demos <% if (!path.match(/^\/$/)) { %>d-none<% } %>">
    <h2>Silk router</h2>
    <p>Silk router is an easy to use plugin for creating single page applications with routing.</p>
    <p>
        <pre>
            <code>
    import { router, route } from 'silkrouter';</code>
        </pre>
    </p>
    <p>
        <pre>
            <code>
    import {router, route} from 'silkrouter';
    route(...);
    router.set(...);</code>
        </pre>
    </p>
    <h3>Installation</h3>
    <p>
        <b>NPM</b>
        <pre>
            <code>
    npm install --save silkrouter</code>
        </pre>
    </p>
    <p>
        <b>CDN</b>
        <pre>
            <code>
    https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/silkrouter@<%=version%>/dist/js/silkrouter.min.js</code>
        </pre>
        OR
        <pre>
            <code>
    https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/silkrouter@<%=version%></code>
        </pre>
    </p>
    <p>
        <b>Please note: </b> Silk router is dependent on <code>deparam.js</code> and <code>lzstorage</code>. You can install these dependencies as follows:
        <pre>
            <code>
    npm install --save deparam.js lzstorage</code>
        </pre>
    </p>
    <h3>How does it work?</h3>
    <p>Silk router provides an API similar to JavaScript events.</p>
    <p><b>Events:</b></p>
    <pre>
        <code>
    $('selector').on('eventName', handler);</code>
    </pre>
    <p><b>Router:</b></p>
    <pre>
        <code>
    route('path', handler);</code>
    </pre>
    <p><b>Trigger an events:</b></p>
    <pre>
        <code>
    $('selector').trigger('event');</code>
    </pre>
    <p><b>Set a route:</b></p>
     <pre>
        <code>
    router.set('path');</code>
    </pre>
    <p>This website is a single page application that uses <b>silk router</b> under the hood. You can check it out how incredibly easy it is to use silk router.</p>
    <p></p>
    <p>Silk router supports following browsers:</p>
    <p><b>IE10+, Edge, Opera, Safari, Chrome, Firefox, Mobile browsers</b></p>
</div>